---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Trademark — protecting Mother's Gold Spice" description="What a trademark is, what to register for a D2C food brand in India, and how to file it yourself for ₹4,500.">
  <main class="bg-cream min-h-screen">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="border-b border-ink/10">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-spice-500 font-medium mb-4">Brand protection</p>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-ink mb-5 leading-tight">Trademark<br/>— protecting the brand</h1>
        <p class="text-ink/70 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed">
          A trademark is legal ownership of the brand identity — the name, logo, tagline, packaging. Without it, anyone can register "Mother's Gold Spice" before us and force a rebrand. This page covers what to file, how, and the ₹4,500 + 1 evening it takes to do it.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-5 text-sm">
          <a href="/plan" class="text-spice underline hover:text-spice-700">← Back to the launch plan</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- WHAT IS A TRADEMARK -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">1. What a trademark actually is</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">In one line: legal ownership of how the brand is identified by customers.</p>

      <p class="tm-body">
        A trademark is the legal protection over four things that make a brand identifiable: the <strong>name</strong>, the <strong>logo</strong>, the <strong>tagline</strong>, and (sometimes) the <strong>packaging design</strong>. Once granted, only the registered owner can use that identity for the registered product category.
      </p>

      <p class="tm-body">
        Without a trademark, the brand "Mother's Gold Spice" is effectively unowned. Anyone who files first becomes the legal owner, and the original creators have to rebrand or pay to use their own name.
      </p>

      <div class="tm-callout">
        <p class="tm-callout-label">The most common founder mistake</p>
        <p>Almost every D2C founder interviewed says <em>"I wish I'd filed the trademark on Day 1."</em> The cost is small (~₹4,500), the work is one evening, and the protection compounds every month the brand grows.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT TO TRADEMARK -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">2. What to trademark for Mother's Gold Spice</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">Four assets, three tiers of priority. File the first one this week.</p>

      <div class="tm-table-wrap">
        <table class="tm-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Asset</th><th>Trademark type</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>"Mother's Gold Spice"</strong> (the name as text)</td><td>Word mark</td><td><span class="tm-tag tm-tag-now">File first</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Wordmark in italic Fraunces script</strong> (the way it's written on the label)</td><td>Device mark</td><td><span class="tm-tag tm-tag-now">File together as combined mark</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Leaf icon + "A FAMILY RECIPE" tagline</strong></td><td>Device mark + slogan</td><td><span class="tm-tag tm-tag-now">Include in combined mark</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Cream label + gold cap (overall jar look)</strong></td><td>Trade dress / 3D mark</td><td><span class="tm-tag tm-tag-later">Year 2 — only if knockoffs appear</span></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="tm-body" style="margin-top: 20px;">
        <strong>For Year 1, file one combined application:</strong> the wordmark + leaf + tagline as a single image. That single ₹4,500 filing protects 90% of what matters. The trade-dress (overall packaging look) only needs separate filing if a competitor copies the entire visual identity later — rare for a small brand in Year 1.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- COST -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">3. What it costs in India (2026)</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">Government fee per class. Pickle = Class 29.</p>

      <div class="tm-table-wrap">
        <table class="tm-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Filer type</th><th>Fee per class</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>Individual / Sole Proprietor</strong></td><td><strong>₹4,500</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>MSME-registered</strong> (Udyam certificate from Phase 1)</td><td><strong>₹4,500</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Startup with DPIIT recognition</td><td>₹4,500</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Private Limited / LLP <em>without</em> MSME</td><td>₹9,000</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-8 mb-3">Which trademark class do you need?</h3>
      <div class="tm-table-wrap">
        <table class="tm-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Class</th><th>What it covers</th><th>For Mother's Gold Spice?</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>Class 29</strong></td><td>Preserved foods, pickles, chutneys, jams, dried fruit</td><td>✓ <strong>Must file</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Class 30</td><td>Sauces, condiments, spices, ready-to-eat masala</td><td>Optional — file if planning a sauce/masala SKU later</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Class 35</td><td>Retail / wholesale / online sales of food products</td><td>Optional — for the storefront brand itself</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Class 43</td><td>Restaurant / food services</td><td>Skip — not relevant for packaged food</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="tm-callout">
        <p class="tm-callout-label">Total cost to protect the brand</p>
        <p><strong>~₹4,500 government fee</strong> for one class (Class 29).</p>
        <p>Optional: ₹3,000–8,000 to a trademark agent if you want hand-holding through the paperwork. Most first-timers can DIY successfully on the IP India portal in one evening.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TIMELINE -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">4. Timeline — long, but protection starts Day 1</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">The full registration takes 12–24 months, but you can use ™ from the moment you file.</p>

      <div class="tm-table-wrap">
        <table class="tm-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Step</th><th>What happens</th><th>Timeline</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>1</td><td>File TM-A application on ipindia.gov.in</td><td>1 day (one evening)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2</td><td>Receive application number → start using ™ on all labels</td><td>Same day</td></tr>
            <tr><td>3</td><td>Trademark Examiner reviews → issues "Examination Report"</td><td>2–6 months</td></tr>
            <tr><td>4</td><td>You respond to any objections (similarity to existing marks, classification issues)</td><td>1 month per response cycle</td></tr>
            <tr><td>5</td><td>Application published in the Trademark Journal</td><td>~6–9 months from filing</td></tr>
            <tr><td>6</td><td>4-month <strong>opposition window</strong> — anyone with conflicting claim can object</td><td>4 months</td></tr>
            <tr><td>7</td><td>Certificate of registration issued → switch to ®</td><td>12–24 months total</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink mt-10 mb-3">When to use ™ vs ®</h3>
      <div class="tm-symbol-grid">
        <div class="tm-symbol-card">
          <div class="tm-symbol-mark">™</div>
          <p class="tm-symbol-title">From the day you file</p>
          <p class="tm-symbol-detail">Signals "we have claimed this trademark." Legally meaningful — gives priority over anyone who files later. Use on labels, website, Instagram, WhatsApp, all marketing material.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tm-symbol-card">
          <div class="tm-symbol-mark">®</div>
          <p class="tm-symbol-title">Only after the certificate arrives</p>
          <p class="tm-symbol-detail">Signals "this is a fully registered trademark." Stronger legal protection — easier to sue copycats. Using ® before registration is technically illegal in India.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="tm-body" style="margin-top: 20px;">
        Use <strong>™</strong> from Day 1 (the day you file). Switch to <strong>®</strong> only after the Certificate of Registration arrives in Year 2.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW TO FILE -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">5. How to file yourself — ~5 hours, one evening</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">No lawyer needed. The full process is online at ipindia.gov.in.</p>

      <ol class="tm-steps">
        <li>
          <p class="tm-step-title">Search if the name is available (10 min, free)</p>
          <p class="tm-step-detail">Go to <a href="https://ipindiaservices.gov.in/tmrsearch/tmrsearch.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="tm-link">ipindiaservices.gov.in/tmrsearch</a> → search "Mother's Gold Spice" in Class 29. If no exact or close matches appear, you're clear to file. Also search variants ("Mothers Gold Spice" without apostrophe, "MGS", etc.).</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="tm-step-title">Decide who owns the trademark</p>
          <p class="tm-step-detail">Recommended: <strong>file in mom's name</strong>. The trademark is the most valuable long-term asset — register it in the name of whoever will permanently own the brand. Transferring later costs paperwork + fees + months of delay. File once, in the right name, forever.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="tm-step-title">Prepare the mark file</p>
          <p class="tm-step-detail">Either: (a) word mark only — just the text "Mother's Gold Spice"; or (b) combined image — the wordmark + leaf + "A FAMILY RECIPE" as a single high-res PNG. Option (b) is stronger because it covers both the name and the visual identity in one application.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="tm-step-title">Create an applicant account on IP India</p>
          <p class="tm-step-detail">Go to <a href="https://ipindiaonline.gov.in/eregister" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="tm-link">ipindiaonline.gov.in/eregister</a> → register as Individual / MSME applicant. Use mom's Aadhaar + PAN. Verify via OTP.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="tm-step-title">File Form TM-A</p>
          <p class="tm-step-detail">Select "New Application" → Form TM-A. Fill in: applicant name (mom), address (her home), trademark image, description, class (29). Upload the mark file. Pay ₹4,500 via netbanking/UPI. You'll get an application number same day.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="tm-step-title">Update labels + branding to add ™</p>
          <p class="tm-step-detail">Update LABEL.md, the wraparound label SVG, the 3D mockups (label-preview), the website footer, Instagram bio, WhatsApp Business profile. Every customer-facing mention of "Mother's Gold Spice" gets the ™ added.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="tm-step-title">Respond to examination report (if any)</p>
          <p class="tm-step-detail">2–6 months later, you'll get an email with the Examiner's report. Most are minor (classification, formatting). Respond on the same portal within 1 month. Major objections (similarity to existing marks) may need a trademark agent — budget ₹3–5k if needed.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="tm-step-title">Wait for Journal publication + Registration certificate</p>
          <p class="tm-step-detail">~12–24 months total. Once the Certificate of Registration arrives, switch from ™ to ® everywhere.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- RISKS OF SKIPPING -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">6. What happens if you skip it</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-6">Two real risks. Neither is theoretical.</p>

      <div class="tm-risk-grid">
        <div class="tm-risk-card">
          <p class="tm-risk-label">Risk 1 — Someone else files first</p>
          <p>"Mother's Gold Spice" is a strong, distinctive name. There is nothing stopping a stranger from registering it next month. If they file before you, <strong>they become the legal owner</strong>. You would have to rebrand, or pay them to license your own brand. Common scam: trademark squatters file marks they suspect a brand will grow into, then sell them back at 10–50× the filing fee.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tm-risk-card">
          <p class="tm-risk-label">Risk 2 — You can't sue copycats</p>
          <p>When a knockoff brand starts selling "Mother's Goldspice Pickle" or "Mom's Gold Spice", without a trademark you have <strong>no legal grounds to stop them</strong>. With a trademark, a single legal notice forces them to rebrand within 30 days. Without it, you're stuck watching them siphon your traffic + reviews + reputation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tm-callout-amber">
        <p class="tm-callout-label">The math is simple</p>
        <p>₹4,500 + 5 hours of your evening = permanent ownership of the brand name. Versus rebranding (₹50k+ in new labels, packaging, marketing) or losing customers to a copycat (immeasurable). <strong>The most asymmetric investment in the entire launch plan.</strong></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WEEK 1 CHECKLIST -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-b border-ink/10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-ink mb-2">7. Three moves for this week</h2>
      <ol class="tm-checklist">
        <li>
          <p class="tm-check-title">Search the name (10 min)</p>
          <p class="tm-check-detail">Visit <a href="https://ipindiaservices.gov.in/tmrsearch/tmrsearch.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="tm-link">ipindiaservices.gov.in/tmrsearch</a> → confirm "Mother's Gold Spice" is genuinely available in Class 29.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="tm-check-title">Confirm the owner — Mom</p>
          <p class="tm-check-detail">MGS trademark gets filed in <strong>Mom's name</strong> — same person as the Sole Proprietor, GSTIN, FSSAI license. One owner across all paperwork. Decision is locked.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="tm-check-title">File TM-A (~1 evening, ₹4,500)</p>
          <p class="tm-check-detail">On <a href="https://ipindiaonline.gov.in/eregister" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="tm-link">ipindiaonline.gov.in/eregister</a>. Upload the combined wordmark+leaf+tagline as one image. Pay online. Get application number same day.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- CLOSING -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 text-center">
      <p class="font-serif text-2xl text-ink leading-relaxed mb-4">
        ₹4,500 today is the best money you'll ever spend on the brand.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mb-8">File it in mom's name. Use ™ everywhere from tomorrow. Sleep peacefully knowing nobody can take "Mother's Gold Spice" away from the family.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
        <a href="/plan" class="px-5 py-2.5 bg-spice text-white text-sm rounded-full hover:bg-spice-700 transition">← Back to the plan</a>
        <a href="/shipping" class="px-5 py-2.5 bg-white border border-ink/15 text-ink text-sm rounded-full hover:bg-mango-50 transition">Shipping economics</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .tm-body {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.8);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .tm-body strong {
    color: #2a1a10;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .tm-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.08);
    background: #fff;
  }
  .tm-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .tm-table th,
  .tm-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.06);
    color: rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.85);
  }
  .tm-table thead th {
    background: #fff8eb;
    font-family: "Fraunces", Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #2a1a10;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #ffe9c2;
  }
  .tm-table tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .tm-table tbody tr:hover { background: #fffbf3; }
  .tm-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 10.5px;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-style: normal;
  }
  .tm-tag-now {
    background: rgba(30, 122, 30, 0.12);
    color: #1e7a1e;
  }
  .tm-tag-later {
    background: rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.08);
    color: rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.6);
  }
  .tm-callout {
    margin-top: 24px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    background: rgba(122, 31, 16, 0.06);
    border-left: 4px solid #7a1f10;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.85);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .tm-callout-amber {
    margin-top: 24px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    background: rgba(224, 135, 18, 0.08);
    border-left: 4px solid #e08712;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.85);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .tm-callout-label {
    font-family: "Fraunces", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #7a1f10;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .tm-callout strong,
  .tm-callout-amber strong {
    color: #2a1a10;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .tm-link {
    color: #7a1f10;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .tm-link:hover { color: #5a1408; }

  /* Symbol comparison cards */
  .tm-symbol-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 14px;
  }
  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .tm-symbol-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
  .tm-symbol-card {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 22px 24px;
    border-radius: 14px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.08);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.04);
  }
  .tm-symbol-mark {
    font-family: "Fraunces", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 56px;
    line-height: 1;
    color: #7a1f10;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .tm-symbol-title {
    font-family: "Fraunces", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #2a1a10;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 6px;
  }
  .tm-symbol-detail {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.7);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Step list (counter-styled) */
  .tm-steps,
  .tm-checklist {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    counter-reset: tmstep;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .tm-steps li,
  .tm-checklist li {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 18px 20px 18px 60px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.08);
    counter-increment: tmstep;
    position: relative;
  }
  .tm-steps li::before,
  .tm-checklist li::before {
    content: counter(tmstep);
    position: absolute;
    left: 16px;
    top: 18px;
    display: inline-flex;
    width: 30px;
    height: 30px;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    background: #7a1f10;
    color: #fff;
    font-family: "Inter", system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 13px;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .tm-step-title,
  .tm-check-title {
    font-family: "Fraunces", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #2a1a10;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 6px;
  }
  .tm-step-detail,
  .tm-check-detail {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.7);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Risk cards */
  .tm-risk-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 14px;
  }
  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .tm-risk-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
  .tm-risk-card {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 20px 22px;
    border-radius: 14px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(122, 31, 16, 0.18);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.04);
  }
  .tm-risk-label {
    font-family: "Fraunces", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: #7a1f10;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .tm-risk-card p:not(.tm-risk-label) {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: rgba(42, 26, 16, 0.75);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .tm-risk-card strong { color: #2a1a10; font-weight: 600; }
</style>
